sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant A as Service A (Sender)
    participant G as AXME Cloud Gateway
    participant R as Runtime + Store
    participant B as Service B (Recipient)
    participant S as Internal Scheduler

    A ->> G: POST /v1/intents (intent_type, payload)
    G ->> R: persist intent, policy_generation = 0
    G ->> B: route to recipient
    G -->> A: 201 accepted + intent_id

    Note over A,G: control mutation (CAS protected)
    A ->> G: POST /intents/{id}/controls or /policy\n(expected_policy_generation = n)
    alt generation matches
        G ->> R: atomic update, generation = n+1
        G -->> A: 200 updated generation
    else generation mismatch
        G -->> A: 409 conflict
        A ->> G: GET /intents/{id}
        G -->> A: latest generation → retry
    end

    Note over B,G: async completion path
    B -->> G: progress / waiting / completion event
    alt WAITING_FOR_HUMAN
        A ->> G: POST /intents/{id}/resume
        G ->> R: continue run
    else WAITING_FOR_TIME
        S -->> R: internal scheduler wakeup
    end
    G -->> A: terminal status
